This is another way to map database id and select fields

```python
class User(SQLAlchemyObjectType):
    class Meta:
        model = UserModel
        interfaces = (relay.Node,)
        only_fields = [
            'id', 'othernames', 'surname', 'email'
        ]

    db_id = graphene.Int()

    @resolve_only_args
    def resolve_db_id(self):
        return self.id
```

A somewhat simple oneway solution is to make SQLAlchemyObjectType.resolve_id return a tuple of the primary keys if it is a list with more than one entry:
```python
    def resolve_id(self, args, context, info):
        graphene_type = info.parent_type.graphene_type
        if is_node(graphene_type):
            keys = self.__mapper__.primary_key_from_instance(self)
            return tuple(keys) if len(keys) > 1 else keys[0]
        return getattr(self, graphene_type._meta.id, None)
```

